// Shadow = a bidirectional evasion Cant [CR#702.28b]: "a creature with shadow
// can't be blocked by creatures without shadow, and a creature without shadow
// can't be blocked by creatures with shadow." Both halves restrict the
// being-blocked relation, so it reads as two Cant(Block) rows over the shadow
// keyword itself (a self-declaring marker — like Flying references Has(Flying),
// the carried name keeps Has(Shadow) matching):
//   - This (shadow) can't be blocked by non-shadow   — on: This, by: ¬shadow
//   - This (shadow) can't block non-shadow            — by: This, on: ¬shadow
// The second row is the contrapositive of "a non-shadow creature can't be
// blocked by shadow," read from This's blocker side.
KeywordAbility(
    name: "Shadow",
    template: "shadow",
    abilities: [Static(effects: [
        Cant(Block(on: Ref(This), by: Not(Has(Shadow)))),
        Cant(Block(by: Ref(This), on: Not(Has(Shadow)))),
    ])],
)
